---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Lightweight Action Recognition Network"
  description="Edge-based real-time human action recognition on an autonomous mobile robot, integrating YOLOv5s, DeepSORT, DLBiLSTM, and TensorRT optimization."
  lang="en"
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container research-detail">
      <a class="back-link" href="/">&larr; Back to Home</a>

      <header class="detail-header">
        <h1 class="detail-title">Lightweight Action Recognition Network</h1>
        <p class="detail-subtitle">
          Edge-based real-time human action recognition on an autonomous mobile robot, integrating detection, tracking, keyframe extraction, and deep learning classification.
        </p>
      </header>

      <!-- Overview -->
      <h2 class="detail-heading">Overview</h2>
      <p class="detail-paragraph">
        This research focuses on edge-based human action recognition for autonomous mobile robots (AMR), aiming to build a real-time, deployable human-robot interaction perception system under limited on-board computing resources. The overall architecture consists of three core modules: human detection and tracking, keyframe extraction, and the action recognition network. The system first captures environmental images via a camera, then uses YOLOv5s and DeepSORT to detect and track individuals. Representative keyframes are extracted from consecutive frames and fed into DenseNet121 combined with a dual-layer bidirectional LSTM (DLBiLSTM) for spatial and temporal feature learning, completing the human action recognition pipeline.
      </p>

      <!-- Research Videos -->
      <h2 class="detail-heading">Research Videos</h2>
      <div class="video-grid">
        <div class="video-wrapper">
          <iframe
            src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/ab0cyBpsyFQ"
            title="Lightweight Action Recognition Network — Research Video 1"
            frameborder="0"
            allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture"
            allowfullscreen
          ></iframe>
        </div>
        <div class="video-wrapper">
          <iframe
            src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/HOViDyvDuTc"
            title="Lightweight Action Recognition Network — Research Video 2"
            frameborder="0"
            allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture"
            allowfullscreen
          ></iframe>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Core Technologies -->
      <h2 class="detail-heading">Core Technologies</h2>
      <ul class="tech-tags">
        <li class="tech-tag">Edge-AI</li>
        <li class="tech-tag">YOLOv5s Human Detection</li>
        <li class="tech-tag">DeepSORT Tracking</li>
        <li class="tech-tag">DLBiLSTM</li>
        <li class="tech-tag">ROS Distributed Computing</li>
        <li class="tech-tag">TensorRT Optimization</li>
      </ul>

      <!-- Research Highlights -->
      <h2 class="detail-heading">Research Highlights</h2>
      <ul class="highlight-list">
        <li class="highlight-item">
          <strong>End-to-end system integration:</strong> Combines human detection, target tracking, keyframe extraction, deep learning classification, and AMR deployment into a complete real-time action recognition pipeline.
        </li>
        <li class="highlight-item">
          <strong>Recognition performance:</strong> Classifies seven types of human actions with average Precision of 97.58%, Recall of 97.49%, and Accuracy of 99.28% in single-action tests.
        </li>
        <li class="highlight-item">
          <strong>Edge computing optimization:</strong> Leverages a ROS distributed architecture and TensorRT model optimization to reduce memory usage and improve inference speed for real-time operation on the AMR.
        </li>
        <li class="highlight-item">
          <strong>On-robot validation:</strong> Continuous action recognition verified on the AMR under stationary, moving, and vSLAM-integrated scenarios, demonstrating feasibility in real-world environments.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <!-- Related Publication -->
      <h2 class="detail-heading">Related Publications</h2>
      <ul class="pub-list">
        <li class="pub-item">
          <strong>王詩婷</strong>、李聯旺、李宜勳，"自主移動機器人動態環境視覺里程計定位技術：一種基於深度學習 DDHAR 動作識別方法," in <em>National Symposium on System Science and Engineering (NSSSE)</em>, 2025.
        </li>
        <li class="pub-item">
          <strong>S.-T. Wang</strong>, I.-H. Li, and L.-W. Lee, "Enhancing Visual Odometry Localization in Dynamic Environments for Autonomous Mobile Robots through Edge DD-HAR: A Deep Learning-Based Action Recognition Approach," in <em>International Conference on Artificial Intelligence and Virtual Reality (AIVR)</em>, 2024.
        </li>
        <li class="pub-item">
          <strong>S.-T. Wang</strong>, I.-H. Li, and L.-W. Lee, "Dynamic Object-Aware Visual Odometry Enhancement for Autonomous Mobile Robots using Edge DD-HAR," in <em>International Conference on System Science and Engineering (ICSSE)</em>, 2024.
        </li>
        <li class="pub-item">
          <strong>S.-T. Wang</strong>, I.-H. Li and W.-Y. Wang,
          "Human Action Recognition of Autonomous Mobile Robot Using Edge-AI,"
          <em>IEEE Sensors Journal</em>, vol. 23, no. 2, pp. 1671-1682, Jan. 15, 2023, doi: 10.1109/JSEN.2022.3225158.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .research-detail {
    max-width: 52rem;
  }

  .back-link {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .back-link:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .detail-header {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-12);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-6);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .detail-title {
    font-size: var(--text-3xl);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-heading);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    line-height: 1.3;
  }

  .detail-subtitle {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .detail-heading {
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-heading);
    margin-top: var(--space-12);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-2);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .detail-paragraph {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.9;
  }

  /* Video grid for multiple videos */
  .video-grid {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-6);
  }

  /* Video embed (responsive 16:9) */
  .video-wrapper {
    position: relative;
    width: 100%;
    padding-bottom: 56.25%;
    height: 0;
    overflow: hidden;
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    background-color: var(--color-bg-secondary);
    box-shadow: 0 4px 12px var(--color-card-shadow);
  }

  .video-wrapper iframe {
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    border: 0;
  }

  /* Tech tags */
  .tech-tags {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: var(--space-2);
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .tech-tag {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: var(--space-1) var(--space-3);
    background-color: var(--color-tag-bg);
    color: var(--color-tag-text);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    font-weight: 500;
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
  }

  /* Highlights */
  .highlight-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-4);
  }

  .highlight-item {
    position: relative;
    padding-left: var(--space-6);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.9;
  }

  .highlight-item::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0.7em;
    width: 0.4rem;
    height: 0.4rem;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background-color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .highlight-item strong {
    color: var(--color-heading);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  /* Publication list */
  .pub-list {
    list-style: disc;
    padding-left: var(--space-6);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-3);
  }

  .pub-item {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .pub-item strong {
    color: var(--color-heading);
  }

  .pub-item em {
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  }
</style>
